quran[9]{c,v,t,f}:
  25,12,"When it sees them from a distant place, they hear its raging and roaring."
  25,13,"And when they are cast, shackled, into a tight place therein, there they plead for demise."
  25,14,"“Do not call<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>for one demise today, but call for many demises.”"
  25,15,"Say<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>, “Is that better or the Garden of Eternity promised to the ones who were mindful<i class=""s"">(of God) </i>? For them it has always been a repayment anda destiny."
  25,16,"They have therein whatever they desire, as they abide. That has always been your<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>Lord’s promise,<i class=""s"">(worthy) </i>to be requested."
  25,17,"And on the day when <span class="h">He{1}</span><span class=""h"">herds</span><span class=""h"">them</span>and what they worship apart from Allah, then <span class=""h"">He</span><span class="h">says{2}</span>, “Was it you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>who misguided these servants of Mine, or was it they who strayed from the way?”",footnotes:1:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Ibn Kathir, Hafs, Abu Ja’far and Ya’qub read it as: “…when We herd them…”</span>],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Ibn Amer read it as: “…then We say,”</span>]
  25,18,"They said{1}, “Highly Exalted are You. We should not <span class="h">have taken any{2}</span>masters apart from You. But you allowed them to enjoy, as well as their fathers, until they forgot the Reminder and became a ruined people.”",footnotes:1:[Frequently the Qur’an addresses the events of the hereafter in past tense; this grammatical shift should be pondered by the reader.],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: Abu Ja’far read it as: “We should not have been taken as masters…”</span>]
  25,19,"Thus they{1}have certainly disbelieved you<a class=""sup""><sup>pl </sup></a>regarding what you say, so <span class="h">you{2}</span><span class=""h"">can neither avoid</span><i class=""s"">(punishment) </i>nor get any support. And whoever of you commits injustice, We will make him taste a supreme punishment.",footnotes:1:[The false masters.],footnotes:2:[<span class="qiraat-footnote">Qira’at: All except for Hafs read it as: “…so they can neither avoid (punishment)…”</span>]
  25,20,"And never did We send any emissaries before you<a class=""sup""><sup>sg </sup></a>but they used to eat food and walk in the marketplaces. And We made some of you a means of trial for others—will you be patient? And your Lord has always been All-Seeing."
